Phase 0: Prerequisites (1-2 Weeks)

Before starting, make sure you're comfortable with:

Java 21
OOP Concepts
Collections Framework
Streams API
Exception Handling
Multithreading Basics
JDBC
SQL

Practice:

CRUD APIs
File handling
Java Records
Functional Programming

Phase 1: Setup the Foundation

Tech Stack

Backend:

Java 21
Spring Boot 3.x
Maven
Spring Data JPA
PostgreSQL
Lombok
Validation API

Tools:

IntelliJ IDEA
Postman
Docker
Git
GitHub

Project Structure:

ecommerce
 ├── controller
 ├── service
 ├── repository
 ├── entity
 ├── dto
 ├── mapper
 ├── exception
 ├── config
 └── util

Learn:

Spring Boot Basics
Dependency Injection
Bean Lifecycle
REST APIs
JPA & Hibernate
DTO Pattern

Build:

Product APIs

POST /products
GET /products
GET /products/{id}
PUT /products/{id}
DELETE /products/{id}

Phase 2: Database Design

Design tables manually.

User
users
------
id
name
email
password
role
created_at
Product
products
---------
id
name
description
price
stock
category_id
Category
categories
-----------
id
name
Cart
cart
----
id
user_id
Cart Item
cart_items
-----------
id
cart_id
product_id
quantity
Order
orders
-------
id
user_id
status
total_amount
created_at
Order Item
order_items
------------
id
order_id
product_id
quantity
price

Learn:

OneToMany
ManyToOne
Cascade Types
Lazy Loading
Eager Loading

Phase 3: Authentication & Authorization

Add:

spring-boot-starter-security

Learn:

JWT
Spring Security
Authentication
Authorization
Filters
Password Encryption

Implement:

/register
/login

Roles:

ADMIN
CUSTOMER

Admin can:

Add Product
Update Product
Delete Product

Customer can:

View Products
Place Orders

Phase 4: Cart Module

Implement:

Add to Cart
Remove from Cart
Update Quantity
View Cart

Endpoints:

POST /cart/items
PUT /cart/items/{id}
DELETE /cart/items/{id}
GET /cart

Learn:

Transactions
Service Layer
Validation

Phase 5: Order Management

Flow:

Add Product
↓
Add To Cart
↓
Checkout
↓
Create Order
↓
Reduce Inventory
↓
Generate Invoice

Learn:

@Transactional

Important concepts:

ACID
Rollback
Concurrency

Phase 6: Exception Handling

Create:

ProductNotFoundException
UserNotFoundException
OutOfStockException

Global Exception Handler:

@RestControllerAdvice

Learn:

Custom Exceptions
Error Response Design

Phase 7: API Documentation

Add:

springdoc-openapi

Generate:

Swagger UI

Learn:

OpenAPI
API Versioning

Phase 8: Testing

Learn:

JUnit 5
Mockito
Integration Testing
TestContainers

Write tests for:

ProductService
CartService
OrderService

Target:

80%+ coverage

Phase 9: Dockerization

Create:

Dockerfile
docker-compose.yml

Run:

Spring Boot
Postgres
Redis

Learn:

Containers
Networking
Volumes

Phase 10: Redis Caching

Cache:

Products
Categories

Learn:

@Cacheable
@CachePut
@CacheEvict

Architecture:

Client
  ↓
Spring Boot
  ↓
Redis
  ↓
Postgres

Phase 11: Async Processing

Learn:

@Async
CompletableFuture

Examples:

Email Notifications
Invoice Generation

Phase 12: Event-Driven Architecture

Add:

Kafka

Events:

OrderCreated
PaymentCompleted
InventoryUpdated

Learn:

Producer
Consumer
Retry Topics
DLQ

This is highly relevant to your current Ola experience.

Phase 13: Payment Integration

Use Sandbox:

Stripe

Flow:

Create Order
↓
Initiate Payment
↓
Payment Success
↓
Update Order Status

Learn:

Webhooks
Idempotency

Phase 14: Search Functionality

Options:

PostgreSQL Full Text Search
Elasticsearch

Search:

/search?query=iphone

Features:

Filters
Sorting
Pagination

Phase 15: Microservices Conversion

Break monolith into:

user-service
product-service
cart-service
order-service
payment-service
notification-service

Learn:

Service Discovery
API Gateway
Config Server
OpenFeign

Phase 16: Cloud Deployment

Deploy on:

AWS EC2
Docker
Nginx

Learn:

CI/CD
GitHub Actions

Pipeline:

Code Push
↓
Build
↓
Test
↓
